article.description: South Carolina St. 77, North Carolina A&T 67
article.headline: South Carolina St. 77, North Carolina A&T 67
article.linkText: South Carolina St. 77, North Carolina A&T 67
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Brian Mason recorded a double-double, 13 points and 11 rebounds, to help lead South Carolina State to a 77-67 win against North Carolina A&T in the teams' Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference season opener Saturday night. Travis Jones led all scorers with 19 points and Derrick Davis added 16 points and five assists for S.C. State (1-5, 0-1 MEAC) to give Jamal Brown his first win as head coach. Sophomore forward Chris Miller-Williams had with 10 points and five rebounds. Trahern Chaplin led the Aggies (2-4, 0-1) with 14 points and five rebounds. Glenn Nelson had 12 points and Jason Wills and Greg Roberts added 11 and 10 points respectively. The Bulldogs jumped out to a 19-3 lead in the first five minutes, but the Aggies answered with a run to cut the lead to just nine on a layup by Greg Roberts at the 11:20 mark. The Bulldogs closed out the half with a 9-1 run that put them up 43-27 at the half. S.C. State led by as many as 21 points at 52-31 in the second half. The Aggies then scored 13 unanswered points to a get to eight points down on a pair of free throws with 11:41 left, but that's as close as they would get.
